      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: forward pending timeout snapshot in waitForAgentJob fallback timer",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes an issue where sub-agent runs killed by their hard timeout (preflight/provider/post_turn) would record `status: timeout` in the registry but the waiting parent session never received the notification. The parent's `agent.wait` downgraded the outcome to a generic soft timeout, losing the hard-phase context.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThe `waitForAgentJob` outer timer only checked `getPendingAgentRunError` and skipped `getPendingAgentRunTimeout`, so pending timeout snapshots were silently dropped. The fix makes the wait-timer fallback symmetric: check the pending timeout snapshot for hard phases while keeping soft phases correctable via retry grace. Reuses the canonical `isHardAgentRunTimeoutPhase` helper instead of rederiving precedence.\n\n## User Impact\nParent sessions now correctly receive hard-timeout completion events for timed-out sub-agents, instead of seeing a generic `gateway_draining`/`queue` timeout with no indication the sub-agent was actually killed by its run timeout.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**E2E (all three hard-timeout phases):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/agent-job.subagent-timeout-notify.e2e.test.ts --run\n ✓ preflight hard-timeout snapshot forwarded\n ✓ provider hard-timeout snapshot forwarded\n ✓ post_turn hard-timeout snapshot forwarded\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  3 passed (3)\n```\n\n**Server methods unit:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  161 passed (161)\n```\n\n**Agent outcome contract:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/agent-run-terminal-outcome.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  14 passed (14)\n```",
        "branch": "fix/issue-89095-subagent-timeout-notify",
